A student is designing a `BankAccount` class that stores a balance and supports deposits. Which of the following designs **best** follows the principle of encapsulation?

**Design A:**
```java
public class BankAccount {
    public double balance;
    public void deposit(double amount) { balance += amount; }
}
```

**Design B:**
```java
public class BankAccount {
    private double balance;
    public void deposit(double amount) { balance += amount; }
    public double getBalance() { return balance; }
}
```

**Design C:**
```java
public class BankAccount {
    private double balance;
    private void deposit(double amount) { balance += amount; }
    private double getBalance() { return balance; }
}
```

**Design D:**
```java
public class BankAccount {
    public static double balance;
    public static void deposit(double amount) { balance += amount; }
}
```

